# Petlove — Cursor Rules
# Drop this file in the project root. Cursor will apply these rules automatically.

## Project Identity
This is "Petlove" — a pet adoption and news React SPA.
Figma: https://www.figma.com/file/puMNfZVg4YI8UZoJ1QiLLi/Petl%F0%9F%92%9Bve
Backend Swagger: https://petlove.b.goit.study/api-docs/

---

## Stack (non-negotiable)
- React 18 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- Vite
- React Router v6 — BrowserRouter, all routes in App.tsx
- Redux Toolkit — configureStore, createSlice, createAsyncThunk
- react-hook-form + Yup — ALL forms, no exceptions
- react-select — location async select in NoticesFilters
- react-toastify — error/success notifications
- axios — with interceptor for Authorization header
- CSS Modules — one .module.css per component

---

## Folder Structure
```
src/
  api/              # axiosInstance.ts + API functions grouped by domain
  assets/
    icons/          # sprite.svg only
    images/         # static page images
  components/       # reusable components (Title, SearchField, Pagination, PetBlock, Modal, Icon, Loader)
  hooks/            # useModal.ts, useAuth.ts, useDebounce.ts
  pages/            # one folder per route
  redux/
    auth/           # authSlice.ts, authThunks.ts, authSelectors.ts
    notices/
    news/
    pets/
    store.ts
  routes/           # PrivateRoute.tsx, RestrictedRoute.tsx
  types/            # all TypeScript interfaces
  utils/            # formatDate.ts, buildQuery.ts
```

---

## Code Rules

### TypeScript
- NEVER use `any` — use `unknown` + type guards or explicit interfaces
- All component props must have a named TypeScript interface (e.g. `interface TitleProps`)
- All API response types defined in src/types/
- Use `FC<Props>` or plain function syntax — never class components

### Components
- One component per file, named export (no default export)
- File name = component name (PascalCase)
- CSS module import: `import css from './ComponentName.module.css'`
- Never write inline styles
- All icons: use `<Icon id="icon-name" width={N} height={N} />` from the sprite — never inline SVG in JSX

### Forms (react-hook-form + Yup)
- Schema defined OUTSIDE the component with `const schema = yup.object({...})`
- Use `useForm({ resolver: yupResolver(schema), mode: 'onBlur' })`
- Show `{errors.fieldName?.message}` below each input
- Never submit to API if form has validation errors

### Validation schemas (copy exactly)
Registration:
  name: yup.string().required('Name is required')
  email: yup.string().matches(/^[\w-]+(\.[\w-]+)*@([\w-]+\.)+[a-zA-Z]{2,7}$/, 'Invalid email').required()
  password: yup.string().min(7, 'Min 7 characters').required()
  confirmPassword: yup.string().oneOf([yup.ref('password')], 'Passwords must match').required()

Login:
  email: (same pattern)
  password: yup.string().min(7).required()

EditUser:
  name: yup.string()
  email: yup.string().matches(/^[\w-]+(\.[\w-]+)*@([\w-]+\.)+[a-zA-Z]{2,7}$/)
  avatar: yup.string().matches(/^https?:\/\/.*\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|gif|bmp|webp)$/, 'Invalid image URL')
  phone: yup.string().matches(/^\+38\d{10}$/, 'Format: +38XXXXXXXXXX')

AddPet:
  title: yup.string().required()
  name: yup.string().required()
  imgUrl: yup.string().matches(/^https?:\/\/.*\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|gif|bmp|webp)$/).required()
  species: yup.string().required()
  birthday: yup.string().matches(/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}$/, 'Format: YYYY-MM-DD').required()
  sex: yup.string().required()

### Redux
- One slice per domain: auth, notices, news, pets
- Async operations: createAsyncThunk only
- Selectors in separate *Selectors.ts file
- NEVER dispatch from inside a reducer
- Persist token: write to localStorage in extraReducers fulfilled, clear on logout

### Routing
- PrivateRoute: if !isLoggedIn → <Navigate to="/login" replace />
- RestrictedRoute: if isLoggedIn → <Navigate to="/profile" replace />
- Sync URL search params for: page, keyword (News), all filters (Notices)

### Modals
- All modals rendered via ReactDOM.createPortal(children, document.body)
- THREE close triggers on EVERY modal: ✕ button, backdrop click, Escape key
- Base Modal component handles all three — page-specific modals use it as wrapper

### API / axios
- Base URL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL (default: https://petlove.b.goit.study/api)
- Request interceptor: attach 'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}` when token exists
- All API calls wrapped in try/catch; errors dispatched to Redux or shown via toast.error()

### Delete operations (pets, favourites)
- NEVER reload the page after delete
- Filter the deleted item from Redux state in extraReducers fulfilled:
  state.items = state.items.filter(item => item._id !== action.payload)

### Responsive breakpoints
- Mobile-first: base styles = mobile (375px)
- Tablet: @media (min-width: 768px)
- Desktop: @media (min-width: 1280px)
- Touch targets: min 44x44px

### Performance
- All images: loading="lazy" + width + height attributes
- Retina: srcSet with 2x image
- Fonts: <link rel="preconnect"> before font stylesheet
- Icon sprite: loaded once, referenced with <use href="...#id">

---

## What NOT to do
- No `console.log` in committed code
- No `any` types
- No inline styles
- No inline SVG icons (use sprite)
- No page reload after delete/toggle
- No Formik (use react-hook-form)
- No `default export` for components
- No hardcoded API URLs (use env variable)
- No `!important` in CSS
- No skipping heading levels in HTML (h1 → h2 → h3)

---

## API Endpoints Reference
POST   /users/register         Register new user
POST   /users/login            Login
POST   /users/logout           Logout (always clear state)
GET    /users/current          Get current user (refresh session)
PUT    /users/edit             Update user profile
POST   /users/pets             Add pet
DELETE /users/pets/:id         Delete pet
GET    /users/notices/favorites   User's favourite notices
GET    /users/notices/viewed      User's viewed notices

GET    /news                   ?page=&limit=&keyword=
GET    /notices                ?page=&limit=&keyword=&category=&sex=&species=&locationId=&sortBy=&sortByOrder=
GET    /notices/:id            Notice detail
POST   /notices/favorites/:id  Add to favourites
DELETE /notices/favorites/:id  Remove from favourites
GET    /notices/categories     List of categories
GET    /notices/sex            List of sex options
GET    /notices/species        List of species
GET    /cities/search          ?value={string} — async location search

GET    /friends                All partner organizations

